**Note on DerivedFrom as edge type vs. EdgeProvenance:** These are EDGE TYPES that describe a relationship between two nodes — e.g., "Graph node A DerivedFrom chunk node B." EdgeProvenance (redesigned in B.3) answers a different question: what source object did this edge itself come from.

