- "unknown" — content that does not fit any listed modality

For each detected modality span:
- span_start and span_end are character offsets within the provided text
- intent_reference describes how the text contains/references/describes the modality

Text chunk (index {}):
{}

Return ONLY a valid JSON array (no explanation, no markdown):
[{{
  "modality": "one of the listed modalities, true_text, or unknown",
  "span_start": 0,
  "span_end": 100,
  "intent_reference": "describes/contains/references/mentions the modality"
}}]"#, modality_list, chunk_index, &chunk_text[..chunk_text.len().min(4000)]);

    let input = serde_json::json!({
        "prompt": prompt,
        "max_tokens": 800,
        "temperature": 0.05,
        "system_context": "Modality detection. Return only valid JSON array.",
