# SECTION D: INITIAL GRAPH CREATION (Before AMT)

## D.1 Overview

Initial graph creation happens **BEFORE AMT building**, not after. This gives AMT access to already-constructed graph evidence for richer intent extraction.

```
INITIAL GRAPH CREATION ORDER

PASS 1 — PARALLEL STRUCTURAL CREATION
  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Create ALL modality graphs simultaneously (structural only):   │
  │                                                                │
  │ TextGraph ──► ModalityGraph[text]      (root + structure)     │
  │ CodeSpans ──► ModalityGraph[code]      (root + structure)     │
  │ MathSpans ──► ModalityGraph[math]      (root + structure)     │
  │ ...etc for all detected modalities...                         │
  │                                                                │
  │ Each graph root node contains:                                 │
  │   - Detection metadata (from RootModalityList)                │
  │   - Evidence references (chunk_index, span_start, span_end)   │
  │   - State: Created                                             │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
PASS 2 — SEMANTIC ENRICHMENT
  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ TEXT FIRST (sequential):                                       │
  │   Add semantic edges + inferred nodes to text graph            │
  │   Text graph now knows which other modality graphs to ref      │
  │                                                                │
  │ ALL OTHERS (parallel after text):                              │
  │   Each modality graph gets semantic enrichment independently   │
  │   Each can reference text graph for back-ref discovery         │
  │                                                                │
  │ State after this pass: SemanticEnriched                        │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
PASS 3 — CROSS-MODAL REFERENCE (Iterative until 5x stable)
  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Round 1: Text → All other modalities                           │
  │   ModalityReference nodes in text graph get edges to           │
  │   corresponding nodes in target modality graphs                │
  │                                                                │
  │ Round 2: All → Text (back-references)                          │
  │   Each modality graph gets back-ref edges to text graph        │
  │                                                                │
  │ Rounds 3-N: Inter-modality (code ↔ math, etc.)               │
  │   Continue until 5 consecutive passes find no new cross-refs   │
  │                                                                │
  │ All bidirectional: stored in respective source graphs          │
  │ State after this pass: CrossLinked → Stable                    │
  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

