# SECTION E: AMT BUILDING (Layer-by-Layer, After Initial Graphs)

## E.1 AMT Building Architecture

The AMT is built **after** initial graphs exist. It works layer by layer — each layer validated independently with a 5x consecutive stable loop. There is no single `build_amt_until_stable` wrapper.

```rust
/// Build the AMT tree layer by layer.
/// Each layer has its own independent 5x consecutive stable validation.
/// AMT can reference initial modality graphs and chunk graphs as evidence.
async fn build_amt_layer_by_layer(
    &self,
    state: &mut OrchestrationState,
) -> OzoneResult<()> {
    let mut current_layer = 0;

    loop {
        current_layer += 1;

        // Build initial content for this layer
        let layer_input = self.gather_layer_input(state, current_layer).await?;
        self.build_amt_layer(state, current_layer, &layer_input).await?;

        // ── Per-layer: 5x consecutive stable validation ──
        let mut layer_stable_count = 0;
        let mut layer_round = 0;

        loop {
            layer_round += 1;

            // Validate layer content
            let new_findings = self.validate_amt_layer(state, current_layer).await?;

            // Cross-reference methodologies for this layer
            let method_findings = self.cross_reference_methodologies_for_layer(
                state, current_layer
            ).await?;

            let has_new = !new_findings.is_empty() || !method_findings.is_empty();

            if has_new {
                layer_stable_count = 0;
                // Expand this layer with new findings
                self.expand_amt_layer(state, current_layer, new_findings, method_findings).await?;
            } else {
                layer_stable_count += 1;
                if layer_stable_count >= 5 {
                    break; // This layer is stable
                }
            }

            // Safety ceiling for individual layer (not overall)
            if layer_round > 50 {
                tracing::warn!("AMT layer {} exceeded 50 validation rounds", current_layer);
                break;
            }
        }

        // Check if there's another layer to build
        let has_next = self.amt_has_pending_sub_intents(state, current_layer).await?;
        if !has_next {
            break;
        }
    }

    state.amt_stable = true;
    Ok(())
}

/// Gather input for building an AMT layer.
/// Uses chunk graphs and initial modality graphs as evidence.
async fn gather_layer_input(
    &self,
    state: &OrchestrationState,
    layer: u32,
) -> OzoneResult<LayerBuildInput> {
    // Aggregate keywords and topics from chunk graphs
    let keywords: Vec<String> = state.chunk_graphs.iter()
        .flat_map(|cg| cg.keywords.clone())
        .collect::<std::collections::HashSet<_>>()
        .into_iter()
        .collect();

    let topics: Vec<String> = state.chunk_graphs.iter()
        .flat_map(|cg| cg.topics.clone())
        .collect::<std::collections::HashSet<_>>()
        .into_iter()
        .collect();

    // Prior layer's intent nodes (parent context)
    let parent_intents = if layer > 1 {
        state.amt.get_layer(layer - 1).cloned().unwrap_or_default()
    } else {
        Vec::new()
    };

    // Graph evidence for this layer
    let graph_summaries = self.summarize_initial_graphs_for_amt(state).await?;

    Ok(LayerBuildInput {
        layer,
        keywords,
        topics,
        parent_intents,
        graph_summaries,
        original_prompt_preview: state.original_prompt[..state.original_prompt.len().min(2000)].to_string(),
    })
}
```

## E.2 Methodology Cross-Reference (Per Layer)

```rust
/// At the end of each layer validation round, cross-reference methodologies.
/// If a layer branch implies a methodology not yet loaded, add it.
/// If no existing methodology covers a branch, synthesize a new one.
async fn cross_reference_methodologies_for_layer(
    &self,
    state: &mut OrchestrationState,
    layer: u32,
) -> OzoneResult<Vec<MethodologyFinding>> {
    let mut findings = Vec::new();

    let layer_branches = state.amt.get_layer(layer).cloned().unwrap_or_default();

    for branch in &layer_branches {
        let required_ids = self.infer_required_methodologies_for_intent(branch).await?;

        for method_id in required_ids {
            if !state.active_methodology_ids.contains(&method_id) {
                // Load this methodology
                match self.load_methodology(method_id).await {
                    Ok(methodology) => {
                        state.active_methodology_ids.push(method_id);
                        state.active_methodologies.insert(method_id, methodology);
                        findings.push(MethodologyFinding::Loaded(method_id));
                    }
                    Err(_) => {
                        // Methodology doesn't exist — synthesize it
                        let new_methodology = self.synthesize_methodology_for_branch(branch).await?;
                        let new_id = self.store_methodology(&new_methodology).await?;
                        state.active_methodology_ids.push(new_id);
                        state.active_methodologies.insert(new_id, new_methodology);
                        findings.push(MethodologyFinding::Created(new_id));
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }

    Ok(findings)
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum MethodologyFinding {
    Loaded(u64),    // existing methodology was added to active set
    Created(u64),   // new methodology was synthesized and stored
}
