# SECTION P: ENGINE TAB UIs

## P.1 Engine Tab Architecture

Engine tabs are injected dynamically — they appear in the tab bar only when a task has graphs of their modality type. Each engine tab is a pipeline that can be invoked directly or used via the UI.

```javascript
/**
 * EnginesTab — Container for all modality engine tabs.
 * Dynamically renders the appropriate engine based on available graphs.
 */

module.exports = {
  meta: {
    title: 'Engines',
    icon: '⚙',
    version: '1.0.0',
  },

  render: function(container, props, React, ReactDOM) {
    const { useState, useEffect } = React;
    const { executePipeline, getSharedState } = props;

    // Engine registry — which modalities have dedicated engines
    const ENGINE_REGISTRY = {
      '3d':             { label: '3D Scene',       icon: '🎬', pipelineId: 109 },
      'eeg':            { label: 'Neural Signal',  icon: '🧠', pipelineId: 108 },
      'bci':            { label: 'BCI',            icon: '⚡', pipelineId: 119 },
      'dna':            { label: 'Genome',         icon: '🧬', pipelineId: 107 },
      'chemistry':      { label: 'Molecular',      icon: '⚗️',  pipelineId: 106 },
      'math':           { label: 'Proof',          icon: '∑',  pipelineId: 105 },
      'code':           { label: 'Code Intel',     icon: '◻',  pipelineId: 101 },
      'parametric_cad': { label: 'CAD',            icon: '📐', pipelineId: 120 },
